('09062a7c-0e8c-4534-bb44-fc1b95865f2f', 'Hoisting in Javascript', '09062a7c-0e8c-4534-bb44-fc1b95865f2f-gdh5sP', NULL, 'When JavaScript’s engine receives a script file and starts executing. The JS engine creates an environment to handle the execution of this JavaScript code. This environment is known as the Global Execution Context. The global execution context goes through two phases – the loading phase, and the execution phase.
