('26dc6bbc-b276-49ce-b18c-246be130544b', 'What are the different data types in JavaScript?', '26dc6bbc-b276-49ce-b18c-246be130544b-H977d2', NULL, 'There are two types of data types. They are – 
Primitive: Primitive data type is not an object or neither has methods and properties. There are seven types of data types in JS. String, number, Boolean, undefined, symbol, null, and ''bigint''. 
Non-primitive data type: In JavaScript object, array, RegEx. By referring to non-primitive data type like object ‘person ={name: ‘ruman’}’, we are actually referring to a memory address that contains the value {name: ‘ruman’}. So that it is mutable.', NULL, 'f', NULL, NULL, '6ffc4a0c-662c-402b-8b5c-420f8de81a87', '2022-07-19 09:39:29', '2022-07-19 09:40:01', '2022-07-19 09:39:29'),
