('86795dcb-aeae-4adc-950e-cfe09710ff04', 'What is Virtual DOM?', '86795dcb-aeae-4adc-950e-cfe09710ff04-norv8C', NULL, 'Virtual DOM is a copy or blueprint of the real DOM kept inside the memory and synced with the real dom. Virtual DOM is the same as real DOM but it doesn’t have the power to directly change the real DOM.
When the browser gets an HTML and CSS file, the browser’s render engine makes the DOM tree and CSSOM tree. Both two tree makes a render tree then this render tree goes through the layout phase where elements coordinates are calculated and finally engine print to display. So when we update something on DOM  the whole process above is recalculated. This is costly. But the virtual DOM is a lightweight replica of the real DOM and when an update occurs in the virtual DOM, React compares the virtual DOM with a snapshot of the virtual DOM taken before the update of the virtual DOM. With the help of this comparison react just update on that particular element. This process is called Diffing.', NULL, 'f', NULL, NULL, '6ffc4a0c-662c-402b-8b5c-420f8de81a87', '2022-07-19 09:30:16', '2022-07-19 09:33:13', '2022-07-19 09:30:16'),
